message: Why don't you declare her an Armenian hero then? Or me an Armenian editor? Maybe Dr. Hans Ernst Jugendorf will also say I'm Armenian, according to which demographic sources I wonder.
I'm against LIES. If someone claims I'm Armenian after I die, I'll turn in my grave. Why are Armenians a spice in every Turkish meatball on Wikipedia?
This reference should be more than enough, but honestly I'm sick of every successful Turk being labeled as possibly Armenian, Jewish or Greek.
It's not "my" opinion, it's "her" opinion. She lost her father while 7 years old, mother while 12 years old, so she definitely must remember who they were. Some people claim Atatürk was Jewish.
Dr. Hans-Lukas Kieser might claim that I'm gay, but as long as "I" know it's not true, it doesn't matter.
